description: Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Don't Ease Me In-> El Paso, Big Railroad Blues, Easy To Love You-> It's All Over Now, Althea, The Music Never Stopped China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Eyes Of The World-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Phil! Second set is a must for any Phil freak. He's out front in the mix and bouncing all over the place. As a result the China->Rider, Eyes sequence is just freakin' sublime. Plus, Jerry's havin' a damn fine night as well.

Phil on + Jerry on = monster show.

Sound quality wavers from three and a half stars at the beginning of set one to a full four stars by mid set two. Thanks to Charlie Miller for all he does.

show is great, BUT...... before downloading individual tracks from above, refer to the TXT file to see what's what, because they are incorrectly listed up there.      

thanks for the good work, i love getting indiana shows, because, seemingly, dead-shows and blind melon are some of the only cool things to have ever happened here :)       lol

Music Never Stopped! Best version ever?  Perhaps... certainly the most Jerry fanning at the end I've eve heard.  Those Phil comments are right on.  I agree about the awesome-ness of the China>Rider, Eyes, too.
,solid 79 show china->ryder one of the better ones from 79. if you have a good system this is a must have. phil is throwin bombs left and right. solid show
lovely sounding show Great China Cat, Eyes, and Space. Amazing how quickly Brent Mydland "clicked" musically w. these guys! '79 was a year w. some really nice shows!

What An Eyes!!! 
As cheerful - no, joyful - as they come, even with a bout of gleeful laughter at the end of the first refrain!
Jerry just loved Eyes, according to his primary biographer (Blair Jackson), and, even in the last  desperate year of the band, it was one of the songs that remained fresh and inventive as ever.
